{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σκοπ-ός</b>, ὁ <br /> (also ἡ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.396, 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Delum” 66)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: (σκέπτομαι):— <b>one that watches, one that looks about</b> or <b>after</b> things, παρὰ δὲ σκοπὸν εἷσεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.359 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; γυναικῶν δμῳάων σ. ἐσσι, of a housekeeper, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” [same place]: in 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], of gods and kings, with <i>genitive</i> loci, <b>guardian, protector</b>, Ὀλύμπου σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “O.” 1.54; Δάλου 6.59 \">Refs</a>]; Μαγνήτων σ., of Peleus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “N.” 5.27; τὸν ὑψόθεν σ., φύλακα βροτῶν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 381 (Lyric poetry); also σκοποὶ τῶν εἰρημένων 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 215. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> <b>one who watches</b> or <b>looks out</b> to take advantage, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.156 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>watchful, jealous master</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 945. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> mostly, <b>lookout-man, watcher</b>, stationed in some high place (σκοπιά) to overlook a country, especially in war, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.792, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.365, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.2.1, 4.1.1, etc.; hence Ἠέλιον.. θεῶν σ. ἠδὲ καὶ ἀνδρῶν “hymnus ad Cererem” 62 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: also, <b>game-watcher</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.40. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>spy, scout</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.324, 526, 561 (later κατάσκοπος) σ. καὶ κατοπτῆρας στρατοῦ ἔπεμψα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 36, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 956 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>a messenger who has been sent to learn tidings</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 35, compare “Ph.” 125; σκοπός, ναῶν κατόπτας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 557 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>mark</b> or <b>object on which one fixes the eye</b>, σκοπὸν ἄλλον, ὃν οὔ πώ τις βάλεν ἀνήρ, εἴσομαι αἴ κε τύχωμι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.6 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπὸ σκοποῦ away from <b>the mark</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11.344 \">Refs</a>]; ἀπὸ σ. εἰρηκέναι, εἰρῆσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 179c, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 2.10; παρὰ σκοπόν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.94 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σκοπῷ ἐπέχειν τόξον to aim at <b>it</b>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 2.89; σκοποῦ ἄντα τυχεῖν [prev. author] “N.” 6.27; ἔκυρσας ὥστε τοξότης.. σκοποῦ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 628; ὥστε τοξόται σκοποῦ, τοξεύετ᾽ ἀνδρὸς τοῦδε 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1033; ἄθλιον σκοπὸν ἐμοὶ ἀκοντίσας 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.3.6; ἐπὶ σκοπὸν βάλλειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.29; παραλλάξαι τοῦ σ. καὶ ἁμαρτεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 194a; ἀποτυγχάνω τοῦ σκοποῦ [prev. author] “Lg.” 744a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>aim, end, object</b>, οὗτος.. δοκεῖ ὁ σ. εἶναι πρὸς ὃν βλέποντα δεῖ ζῆν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Grg.” 507d; τὴν ἡδονὴν σ. ὀρθὸν πᾶσι ζῴοις γεγονέναι [prev. author] “Phlb.” 60a; στοχάζεσθαι σκοποῦ [prev. author] “R.” 519c; σ. τυραννικὸς τὸ ἡδύ 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1311a4, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; σκοπός.. <b>nihil praebere</b> 'his little game' is to make no allowance, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Cicero, M. Tullius Orator et Philosophus “Epistulae ad Atticum” 15.29.2, compare argument 11 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Eq.” \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> in Medicine texts, of healing, ἐπὶ τῷ πρώτῳ σ. by first <b>intention</b> (i.e. direct union), κατὰ δεύτερον σ. by second <b>intention</b> (i.e. granulation or scar tissue), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 1.387, compare 10.162. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>contest in shooting at a mark</b>, σ. ἱππέων, πεζῶν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 9(2).527.16,18 (from Larissa). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> name of <b>a dance</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 446. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4649","accentedUnicode":"σκοπός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4648","matchingForm":"σκοπέω","stepTransliteration":"skopeō","gloss":"to watch out","_zh_tw_Gloss":"小心","_es_Gloss":"estar alerta","_zh_Gloss":"小心"}],"shortDef":"goal","mediumDef":"<b>a watcher;</b>, also, <b>a distant object on which the eye is kept fixed; a mark, goal,</b> <ref='Php.3.14'>Phil. 3:14</ref>*","stepGloss":"goal","stepTransliteration":"skopos","count":1,"_es_Definition":"meta ; hacia la meta (FIL.3:14)","_zh_tw_Definition":"目標","_zh_Definition":"目标","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"mục đích; đích nhắm; nhắm mục đích","_zh_tw_Gloss":"標竿","_es_Gloss":"meta","_zh_Gloss":"标竿"}]}